A MAN is in a serious condition in hospital after being run over and shot in a suspected gang related hit last night.
Glasgow’s Royston Road was sealed of by police after the incident at around 6.30pm.
A Police Scotland spokesman said: “A 29-year-old man was run over by a white Mitsubishi 4x4 and then shot by one of the occupants.
“The car was later recovered in the Royston area.
“The victim is detained in hospital in a serious but stable condition.”
